name: JSONParser
description: Represents a parser for JSON-encoded content.

getblobvalue().name: getBlobValue
getblobvalue().description: Returns the current token as a BLOB value.

getbooleanvalue().name: getBooleanValue
getbooleanvalue().description: Returns the current token as a Boolean value.

getcurrentname().name: getCurrentName
getcurrentname().description: Returns the name associated with the current token.

getcurrenttoken().name: getCurrentToken
getcurrenttoken().description: Returns the token that the parser currently points to or null if there's no current token.

getdatetimevalue().name: getDatetimeValue
getdatetimevalue().description: Returns the current token as a date and time value.

getdatevalue().name: getDateValue
getdatevalue().description: Returns the current token as a date value.

getdecimalvalue().name: getDecimalValue
getdecimalvalue().description: Returns the current token as a decimal value.

getdoublevalue().name: getDoubleValue
getdoublevalue().description: Returns the current token as a double value.

getidvalue().name: getIdValue
getidvalue().description: Returns the current token as an ID value.

getintegervalue().name: getIntegerValue
getintegervalue().description: Returns the current token as an integer value.

getlastclearedtoken().name: getLastClearedToken
getlastclearedtoken().description: Returns the last token that was cleared by the clearCurrentToken method.

getlongvalue().name: getLongValue
getlongvalue().description: Returns the current token as a long value.

gettext().name: getText
gettext().description: Returns the textual representation of the current token or null if there's no current token.

gettimevalue().name: getTimeValue
gettimevalue().description: Returns the current token as a time value.

hascurrenttoken().name: hasCurrentToken
hascurrenttoken().description: Returns true if the parser currently points to a token; otherwise, returns false.

nexttoken().name: nextToken
nexttoken().description: Returns the next token or null if the parser has reached the end of the input stream.

nextvalue().name: nextValue
nextvalue().description: Returns the next token that is a value type or null if the parser has reached the end of the input stream.

readvalueas(system.type).name: readValueAs
readvalueas(system.type).description: Deserializes JSON content into an object of the specified Apex type and returns the deserialized object.

apextype.name: apexType
apextype.description: The apexType argument specifies the type of the object that this method returns after deserializing the current value.

readvalueasstrict(system.type).name: readValueAsStrict
readvalueasstrict(system.type).description: Deserializes JSON content into an object of the specified Apex type and returns the deserialized object. All attributes in the JSON content must be present in the specified type.

apextype.name: apexType
apextype.description: The apexType argument specifies the type of the object that this method returns after deserializing the current value.

skipchildren().name: skipChildren
skipchildren().description: Skips all child tokens of type JSONToken.START_ARRAY and JSONToken.START_OBJECT that the parser currently points to.
